1.0.name: wordpress/fb-linkedin-resume
1.0.description:
This plugin uses a new way of processing your LinkedIn profile to extract all the information you need to publish on your blog. Using HTML DOM parsing we avoid all the possible bugs and malfunctions due to regular expression parsing, this way we're way more sure that our plugin is absolutely resistant to all the LinkedIn HTML changes that could occur in the future.

It also outputs the LinkedIn HTML parts instead of creating new HTML, this way we're sure that it supports and will support all possible LinkedIn options for every part of your profile.

It features two ways of usage:

  1. Just print out the whole profile without customizations.
  2. Extract single parts of your profile and print each one where you want.

Supported shortcodes:

  • fb_linkedin_resume_full: prints all your LinkedIn public profile.
  • fb_linkedin_resume_header: prints the upper badge.
  • fb_linkedin_resume_summary: prints the "summary" section.<
